name: Bug fixes
body: Several fixes have been made to improve plugin data accuracy.

name: OpenVPN plugin, vms plugin improvement
body: New openvpn plugin and added cpu_percentage metric to vms plugin (for easier alerts setup).

name: php-fpm multiple pools
body: php-fpm multiple pools support, separate pools by comma (,) in /etc/nixstats.ini

name: Monitor directory sizes
body: New plugin for monitoring directory sizes. (Linux only)

name: NVME/Smartmontools plugin
body: Keep track of your HDD/SSD/NVME health with this plugin. Requires the agent to be run under the root user.

name: New plugins & plugin fixes
body:
Improved plugins:
vms
temp
litespeed

New plugins:
Elasticsearch (experimental)
GPU Temp (Windows only, experimental)

name: 3 New monitoring plugins
body: RabbitMQ, Exim mail queue and Redis plugin.

name: Let user choose disk usage parser
Caching failed API calls
body: Failed API data calls will be retried now.

name: Bug fixes
body: Some minor bugfixes regarding parameters when using nixstatsagent

name: Improved support for custom plugins
body:
Added baseline caching feature for custom plugins.
NGiNX plugin
New parameters: --version, --help, --test (plugin) for nixstatsagent.py

name: Windows compatibility fixes
body: Also new plugins and `hello` (server token utility).

name: Python 2.4 compatibility and build automation release
1.0 distribution fix
body: The package (source distribution and 2.7 egg and wheel) are now available from PyPI.

name: The first wide distribution release
body: This release is prepared with Python setuptools in mind. It should be feasible now to install the software from PyPI, and it would streamline any further packaging tasks.
